result.execSummary:
The defendant Erich Paul Vanstrom was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 2nd-Degree Recklessly Endangering Safety, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.30(2).
  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Sentencing hearing on November 2, 2016 at 11:00 am.

Defendant Erich Paul Vanstrom in court with attorney Erik C. Johnson.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that there will be a plea today but parties will be requesting a sentencing date.  Atty Hendee files an amended information with the court to amend Ct. 1 to 2nd Degree Recklesslyt Endangering Safety 941.30(2).
Atty Johnson agrees.
BY THE COURT:  Count 1 will be amended to 2nd Degree Recklesslyt Endangering Safety 941.30(2).
  Atty Hendee states plea agreement to the amended Ct. 1 and Ct. 5.  Counts 2, 3 & 4 to be dismissed and read-in.
Atty Johnson agrees and enters a No Contest plea.  Defendant agrees.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.  

Atty Hendee states that parties are not requesting a PSI.  Atty Johnson aes.

BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of the amended Ct. 1 and Ct. 5.  Counts 2, 3 & 4 to be dismissed and read-in.
Set for Sentencing
bond continued.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for November 2, 2016 at 11:00 am.
